The bug is that after every inner loop iteration, it's setting `total` to b
be equal to the current `entry.amount`, which means `total` will only ever 
store the last value in each sub-group of entries. Instead, you should add 
`entry.amount` to `total` rather than just assigning a new value to `total`
`total`. 

Here is the fixed Tundra code:

```tundra
val groups = [
  {
    name: "north",
    entries: [
      { amount: 2 },
      { amount: 3 }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: "south",
    entries: [
      { amount: 4 }
    ]
  }
];

var total = 0;
for (group in groups) {
  for (entry in group.entries) {
    total = total + entry.amount;
  }
}

print(total);
```
This code will now correctly calculate the sum of all `entry.amount`s and p
print out the expected output: 9.
